author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
---

1 unit Lemon
2 clove Garlic
¼ ounce Parsley
6 ounce Green Beans
11 ounce Tilapia
1 tablespoon Fry Seasoning
½ cup Israeli Couscous
½ ounce Almonds
2 tablespoon Garlic Herb Butter
1 teaspoon Chili Flakes
4 tablespoon Olive Oil
Salt
Pepper

Adjust rack to top position (top and
middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a
medium pot of salted water to a boil.
Wash and dry all produce. Zest and
quarter lemon (for 4, zest 1 lemon and
quarter both). Mince or grate garlic.
Finely chop parsley. In a small bowl,
combine parsley, 3 TBSP olive oil (5
TBSP for 4), a pinch of garlic and lemon
zest, and lemon juice to taste. Season
with salt and pepper; set aside.

Toss green beans on one side of a
baking sheet with a drizzle of olive oil,
salt, and pepper. Pat tilapia dry with
paper towels; rub all over with olive oil,
Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper. Place
on empty side of same sheet. Roast on
top rack until tilapia is cooked through
and green beans are tender, 12-15
minutes. (For 4 servings, divide between
2 baking sheets; roast green beans on
top rack and tilapia on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, once water is boiling,
add couscous to pot. Cook until tender,
6-8 minutes. Drain thoroughly. Melt
garlic herb butter in empty pot over
medium heat. Return couscous to pot
and stir until coated. Taste and season
with salt and pepper. Turn off heat;
keep covered until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat a
medium, dry pan over medium-high
heat. Add almonds and toast, stirring
occasionally, until golden brown, 2-4
minutes. Turn off heat. Transfer to
a cutting board; finely chop half the
almonds.

Stir chopped almonds into bowl
with gremolata. Add a small pinch of
chili flakes if desired. Season with salt,
pepper, and a squeeze of lemon juice
to taste.

Divide couscous, green beans, and
tilapia between plates. Spoon almond
parsley gremolata over tilapia. Scatter
remaining almonds over green beans;
add a pinch of chili flakes if desired.
Serve with any remaining lemon
wedges on the side.